This paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) tasks and proposes a Bayesian generative model for the space of neural parameters to enable zero-shot classification on unseen task-language combinations. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves machine learning techniques, such as neural networks and variational inference, which are relevant to sub-categories cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Additionally, the paper experiments with a typologically diverse sample of languages, which could be relevant to sub-category cs.CV (Computer Vision) if the languages involve visual data.
